# Configuration Cursor Rules
# Rules for configuration files and settings

## Configuration Management
- Use environment-specific config files
- Keep sensitive data in environment variables
- Document all configuration options
- Use validation for configuration values

## File Formats
- Prefer YAML for human-readable configs
- Use JSON for programmatic configs
- Add comments explaining complex settings
- Use consistent naming conventions

## Security
- Never commit secrets to version control
- Use proper file permissions for config files
- Implement config validation at startup
- Rotate secrets regularly

## Organization
- Group related configuration options
- Use hierarchical structure for complex configs
- Provide sensible defaults
- Include example configuration files